Queue Management (AQM)
2016", shape=ellipse, URL="RFC7928.html", target="_top", tooltip="Unmanaged large buffers in today's networks have given rise to a slew of performance issues.  These performance issues can be addressed by some form of Active Queue Management (AQM) mechanism, optionally in combination with a packet-scheduling scheme such as fair queuing.  This document describes various criteria for performing characterizations of AQM schemes that can be used in lab testing during development, prior to deployment."];
