2018", shape=ellipse, URL="RFC8289.html", target="_top", tooltip="This document describes CoDel (Controlled Delay) -- a general framework that controls bufferbloat-generated excess delay in modern networking environments.  CoDel consists of an estimator, a setpoint, and a control loop.  It requires no configuration in normal Internet deployments."];
